# Ngo Boat Race — Soc Trang

Rhythm-racing H5 game (Vite + TypeScript + Phaser 3 + Fastify API). Inspired by **Oóc Om Bóc** / Khmer Ngo boat festival on the **Maspéro River**, Soc Trang.

## Run locally

```bash
npm install
npm run dev:all   # game :5173, API :3000
```

## Conventions

- **Default language: English** — toggle EN/VN via top-right `LangToggle`
- ESL-friendly English in UI; avoid gaming slang
- Terminology: **Rhythm** (drum timing), **Crowd cheer** (finish burst), **Maspéro** (river name)
- **Beta** — do not git commit unless the user explicitly asks
- Minimize diff scope; match existing patterns in surrounding code

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/` | Game client — Phaser scenes, DOM UI, i18n, rhythm engine |
| `server/` | Fastify API — leaderboard, daily seed, guest auth, JSON file DB |
| `src/content/festival/` | Canonical Festival article (en.md, vi.md) |
| `tests/unit/` | Vitest — run `npm test` before push |

## Architecture split

- **Phaser (canvas):** race visuals — water, boats, parallax
- **DOM (HTML):** menus, HUD, Settings, Festival scroll, i18n
- Race input captured on DOM → sent to `RaceController`
